<h2>Hash Lookup and Rainbow Table Awareness</h2>

<p>Unsalted MD5 and SHA-1 hashes of common strings (passwords, phrases, words) appear in publicly available rainbow tables and can be reversed in seconds. Any hash you generate using a simple string without a salt is potentially reversible if the input is predictable. This is why password hashing libraries always add a random salt before hashing — the salt makes each hash unique even for identical passwords and defeats precomputed lookup tables.</p>

